// Search 02 — bolder steps out of the sieve plateau.
//
// Search-01 (docs/research/sweeps/2026-07-13-search-01.md) found the
// chains/sieve neighborhood is a fitness plateau under single sigma=0.3
// mutations: five generations climbed 1%. This spec applies its
// instrument lessons via search v1.1 (Q-2026-07-14-A):
//
// - mutations_per_child: 3 and sigma 0.6 — compound, larger steps, the
//   cheapest plateau escape that bends no metric (finding 1);
// - confirm_bond_cap: 600000 — sieve-class regimes carry ~150k bonds at
//   3k ticks and grow roughly linearly, so a 6k confirmation expects
//   ~300k; x2 headroom keeps honest champions uncapped while still
//   bounding a runaway (finding 3's sizing rule: cap ~ expected bonds at
//   THAT horizon x headroom);
// - screen bond_cap unchanged at 200k (~10x a healthy sieve screen);
// - same seeds, screen horizon, and observer as search-01, so the two
//   searches differ ONLY in step size and the confirmation cap — a
//   controlled comparison of local vs bolder search on the same ground.
//
// Budget: 2 seeds + 6 generations x 10 children = 62 screens at 3k
// ticks, top 2 confirmed at 6k.
//
//   genesis search --spec sweeps/search-02.ron --out <dir>
#![enable(implicit_some)]
(
    seed: 20260714,
    generations: 6,
    population: 10,
    survivors: 3,
    sigma: 0.6,
    mutations_per_child: 3,
    screen_ticks: 3000,
    every: 100,
    confirm_ticks: 6000,
    confirm_top: 2,
    bond_cap: 200000,
    confirm_bond_cap: 600000,
    seeds: [
        (
            name: "chains",
            rules: "packs/chains.ron",
        ),
        (
            name: "sieve",
            config: Some("configs/sieve.ron"),
            rules: "packs/sieve.ron",
        ),
    ],
)
